開放式課程






















標題: 網路安全  （英文授課）Network Security
作者: 邵家健Open Education Office開放教育推動中心
公開日期: 2011
摘要: 課程首頁
 
本課程是由交通大學資訊工程學系提供。
 
This course will cover three basic aspects of Internet security: 

Cryptography - including hash functions, symmetric &amp; asymmetric cryptosystems; 
Communication Security Services - including confidentiality, integrity, authentication &amp; access control; 
Internet Security Practices - including firewalls &amp; virtual private networks.課程目標/概述  
This course will cover three basic aspects of Internet security: 

Cryptography - including hash functions, symmetric &amp; asymmetric cryptosystems; 
Communication Security Services - including confidentiality, integrity, authentication &amp; access control; 
Internet Security Practices - including firewalls &amp; virtual private networks. 
 
課程章節  




單元主題

內容綱要


Part I Introduction
1.1 Basic Concepts1.2 Security Services &amp; Mechanisms


Part IICryptography &amp; Security Mechanisms
2.1 Encipherment


Part IIISecurity Operations and Protocols
3.1 Infrastructure, Key Distribution Center (KDC)3.2 Infrastructure, Public Key Infrastructure (PKI)3.3 IP Security Protocols (IPsec)3.4 Internet Key Management Protocols


Part IVInternet Security Practices　
4.1 Firewalls4.2 Virtual Private Networks (VPNs)
 
課程書目  

William Stallings, "Network Security Essentials - Applications and Standards", 4th Ed., Pearson Education, January 2011.
Charles Kaufman, Mike Speciner, Radia Perlman,"Network Security: Private Communication in a Public World" [2nd Ed.], Pearson Education, April 2002. (ISBN: 0130460192, 752 pages) 
 
參考書目  

William Stallings, "Cryptography and Network Security - Principles &amp; Practice", 5th Ed., Pearson Education, January 2010. 
Warwick Ford, "Computer Communication Security: Principles, Standard Protocols &amp; Techniques", Prentice Hall, September 1993. (ISBN: 0137994532, 528 pages) 
Naganand Doraswamy, Dan Harkins, "IPSec - The New Security Standard for the Internet, Intranets and Virtual Private Networks", Prentice Hall, 1999. (ISBN: 0130118982, 222 pages) 
Ross Anderson, "Security Engineering: A Guide to Build Dependable Distributed Systems" [2nd Ed.], John Wiley, April 2008. (ISBN: 0470068523, 1080 pages)
 
